description: The US DHS announced that Indian doctoral student Ranjani Srinivasan from Columbia University self-deported after her visa was revoked for alleged Hamas support. Her departure follows increased scrutiny of foreign students in the US amidst pro-Palestinian protests on campuses.
title: Indian scholar at Columbia univ self-deports after visa revocation over Hamas ties
175 answersheets burnt in fire after teacher takes them home
Hyderabad: 3,500-year-old Mudumal menhirs make it to Unesco tentative list

description: Tesla has initiated the certification and homologation process for the Model Y and Model 3 in India as required to enter the market. The Indian EV market is growing, with sales increasing by 20%, due to government initiatives and subsidies.
title: Tesla seeks certification for 2 EV models in India

description: A 60-year-old businesswoman was deceived into investing 2.8 crore in a sham coffee powder company, persuaded by her brother with promises of high returns. Trusting the alleged involvement of cricketer Chris Gayle, she and others suffered significant financial losses, receiving only 90 lakh out of the 5.7 crore investment.
title: 60-year-old duped of Rs 2.8 crore by brother using Chris Gayle’s name
Indo-Russian chamber official held in fraud case

description: Nasa and SpaceX are set to launch the Crew-10 mission on Thursday, which will send a four-member crew to the ISS. This mission will facilitate the return of veteran astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore, who have been stranded on the ISS since June due to technical issues.
title: Nasa, SpaceX to launch Crew-10 mission to bring back Sunita Williams, Wilmore
JD Vance's joke on wife Usha backfires as social media users suggest: 'Usha, run'

description: Quinnipiac University's poll says Trump has a 42 per cent approval rating compared to a 53 per cent disapproval rating. The poll was taken from March 6-11, among 1,198 "self-identified registered voters." It has a margin of error of 2.8 per cent. A month before, Trump's disapproval rating was 49 per cent and approval rating was 45 per cent.
title: Donald Trump's approval rating drops since election, Nate Silver explains why

description: The entertainment world is buzzing with major updates! From Gauri Pratt discussing meeting Aamir Khan's family and marriage plans to the passing of Ayan Mukerji’s father, Deb Mukherjee, and Tamannaah Bhatia and Vijay Varma’s Holi celebrations at Raveena Tandon's house—here are the top five entertainment stories of the day that have everyone talking!
title: Gauri Pratt on meeting Aamir Khan's family and marriage plans
Gene Hackman’s will excludes children, now his $80m fortune hangs in the balance

description: This is not the first time that Elon Musk's ex and X's mother made it clear how she feels about her son getting so much exposure all of a sudden. When X was all over the Oval Office when his father joined Donald Trump in a press conference, Grimes said he should not be public like this.
title: Grimes says she's begging Elon Musk to not make their son X's life public: 'No way to deal with this'
Just hours after Trump's appeal to spare lives, Putin tells Ukraine troops in Kursk to surrender

description: Travis Kelce made a playful shoutout to his girlfriend Taylor Swift during a bonus episode of his podcast with brother Jason. He sang a line from Swift's song '22' and wore a 'Tribeca' hat, sparking fan speculations. The couple, keeping a low profile, were recently seen on a date night in Park City, Utah.
title: Travis Kelce Sends Swifties Into a Frenzy by Singing Taylor Swift’s '22'

description: Elon Musk stirred controversy by sharing a post suggesting mass killings under Hitler, Stalin, and Mao were carried out by public sector workers, not the dictators themselves. The post has been criticized, with Lee Saunders, AFSCME president, condemning the implication. This follows Musk's previous backlash over a gesture resembling a Nazi salute at Trump's second inauguration.
title: Elon Musk resharing post saying 'Hitler didn’t murder millions, ...' sparks controversy
Mark Carney formally sworn in as Canada PM, replacing Trudeau

description: Infosys founder Narayana Murthy addressed the growing AI trend in India, cautioning against overhyping 'ordinary' programs as AI. He explained the principles of machine learning and deep learning and emphasized their potential. While acknowledging job displacement, he highlighted AI's opportunities in creating new professions, particularly in autonomous vehicles and other sectors.
title: Narayana Murthy warns against the rise of AI

description: Four teenage boys, students of Class X, drowned in the Ulhas river in Thane's Badlapur area after Holi celebrations on Friday. They were swept away by the sudden rise in the water level. The victims have been identified, and their bodies have been recovered and sent for post-mortem. An investigation is underway.
title: Four teenage boys drown in river after Holi celebrations in Thane

description: Joshua Riibe, the man who was last seen with Sudiksha Konanki, claims he rescued Sudiksha Konaki from rough Caribbean waters but cannot explain her subsequent disappearance. Riibe told police he fell asleep after vomiting seawater and did not see her again. Police are investigating potential foul play, and Riibe has declined to answer further questions on his lawyer's advice.
title: New twist in Sudiksha Konanki disappearance case

description: Donald Trump's tariff moves have taken the world by storm - the US economy too is staring at uncertainty as the impact of high tariffs on countries around the world is unknown. Economists have expressed concern of a likely US recession like scenario. In such a case, should India be worried? We take a look:
title: Trump tariffs impact: Is a US recession likely and does India need to worry?
Vadodara tragedy: Woman crushed in drunken hit-and-run - 10 points to know

description: Skywatchers in the US will have the chance to witness a rare total lunar eclipse on Thursday night, resulting in a Blood Moon. The event will last about six hours, with totality occurring at 2:26 AM EDT on Friday and best views across North and South America.
title: Blood Moon & Total Lunar Eclipse visible in US: Time, how to watch and more

description: Portugal won't buy Lockheed Martin F-35s from the United States though the country's air force gave a go-ahead for that. The country now wants to take into account other situational aspects and President Donald Trump is one of them. Citing Portuguese media Publico, Politico reported that outgoing defence minister Nuno Melo shot down the proposal of buying F-35s from the US because of Donald Trump.
title: 'Because of Donald Trump': Portugal rules out buying F-35s from US
'Good chance war can finally end': Trump talks to Putin, urges him to spare Ukrainian lives
'Senior ISIS leader Abu Khadija killed in joint US-Iraq op'

description: LeBron James suffered a groin injury during the Los Angeles Lakers vs. Boston Celtics game and will miss 1-2 weeks. He is optimistic about his recovery and will take proper measures to heal. Luka Doncic will lead the team in his absence as the Lakers aim to secure a strong playoff position.
title: When Will the Los Angeles Lakers Star Return After Groin Injury?

description: In a violent attack at the Golden Temple, Amritsar, five individuals were assaulted by a man wielding an iron rod during the New Nanakshahi Year celebrations. The assailant, identified as Julfan from Haryana, seriously injured two victims. He was apprehended with the help of CCTV footage and handed over to the police.
title: Attack at Golden Temple: Man wielding iron rod injures 5 devotees

description: A bomb explosion during Friday prayers at a South Waziristan mosque injured four, including JUI district chief Maulana Abdullah Nadeem. The blast occurred at Maulana Abdul Aziz Mosque, with an IED planted in the pulpit. Security officials are investigating the site, with no group claiming responsibility yet. Khyber Pakhtunkhwa mosques have been frequently targeted during Friday prayers.
title: Blast at Pakistan mosque, Islamist leader among 4 hurt

description: David Warner, set to debut in The Hundred with London Spirit, remains unfazed by potential boos from English fans. He relishes the challenge and excitement such reception brings. Though retired from international cricket, Warner remains critical of 'Bazball,' questioning its effectiveness in Australian conditions. Warner has often encountered a hostile reception in England, with tensions reaching a peak during the 2023 Ashes at Lord’s following Jonny Bairstow’s controversial stumping.
title: 'Boo me, but don't boo the team': David Warner

description: Former India wicketkeeper-batter Dinesh Karthik has credited the IPL with transforming Indian cricket by fostering a winning mentality and improving infrastructure. Karthik emphasised the depth of talent in Indian cricket, allowing the country to field multiple competitive teams simultaneously. He highlighted the confidence-building experiences IPL provides by allowing players to compete alongside global legends.
title: 'Can field 2-3 teams at same time': DK credits IPL for revolutionising Indian cricket

description: Mumbai Indians reached their second Women's Premier League final by defeating Gujarat Giants by 47 runs. The celebration featured both captains, Harmanpreet Kaur and Hardik Pandya, sharing a joyful moment. The win included standout performances from Nat Sciver-Brunt and Hayley Matthews. Mumbai Indians will now face Delhi Capitals in the title match.
title: Captain meets Captain! Harmanpreet, Hardik share MI's winning vibe - Watch

description: Veteran actor Deb Mukherjee passed away at 83 on March 14, 2025. Bollywood celebrities including Kajol, Jaya Bachchan, Ranbir Kapoor, and Alia Bhatt visited the Mukerji residence to offer their condolences. His funeral will be held at Pawan Hans Crematorium in Juhu. Mukherjee was known for his roles in 'Abhinetri' and 'Ek Baar Muskurado.'
title: Celebrities arrive at Ayan Mukerji’s home to pay their last respects to Deb Mukherjee
Ex-Cong MLA Bamber Thakur shot at in Chhattisgarh
Gold smuggling case: Ranya Rao's bail plea rejected

description: The Karnataka High Court stayed the trial court's decision to take cognizance of charges against former Chief Minister B.S. Yediyurappa and three others in a Pocso Act case. The stay, pending further hearings, exempts them from personal appearances following an appeal that questioned the complaint's validity.
title: Pocso case: K'taka HC stays summons against Yediyurappa

description: Sana Khan has received hateful comments on social media about herself and her family, including her son. She addressed these trolls, criticizing the lack of education and civility in such remarks. Additionally, Sana faced backlash after a viral video showed her questioning Sambhavna Seth's attire, which was seen as imposing religious beliefs.
title: Sana Khan slams trolls attacking her son and husband

description: In 2015, journalist Vimal Kumar became part of an unexpected viral moment when two Australian women kissed him live on TV during a broadcast. Orchestrated by his photographer, the prank video has remained a popular clip on the internet. Kumar, a veteran sports reporter, continues to share insights through his YouTube channel.
title: The inside story of two Australian woman kissing an Indian journalist on live TV

description: Aamir Khan introduced his girlfriend, Gauri Spratt, at a pre-birthday event in Mumbai. They have been dating for over a year and decided to make their relationship public. Gauri hails from Bengaluru and manages a salon in Mumbai. She has been involved in Aamir's professional life and met his family and friends.
title: Who is Gauri Spratt: Aamir Khan introduces his Bengaluru-based girlfriend

description: Two forest watchers at Kanha National Park in Madhya Pradesh have been arrested under UAPA for allegedly aiding Maoists. Their detention has caused unrest among forest staff, leading to fears of being caught between insurgents and law enforcement. The arrests raise concerns about the infiltration of insurgents within wildlife sanctuaries, impacting both security and conservation efforts.
title: From daredevils to 'anti-nationals': Forest watchers face UAPA charges

description: A fire at the Atlantis Building in Rajkot, Gujarat, killed three people and injured one. Emergency services quickly responded and evacuated all residents. The fire has been controlled, and the injured person is receiving medical treatment. The names of the deceased have not yet been released, and further details are expected soon.
title: 3 dead after fire broke out at Rajkot's Atlantis building

description: Following his World Chess Championship victory, D Gukesh visits the Tirumala Temple in Andhra Pradesh, shaving his head to seek blessings. This traditional act signifies devotion and humility. Gukesh remains focused on upcoming tournaments in 2025, aiming for continuous improvement. His spiritual gesture has garnered appreciation online, with many praising his adherence to tradition.
title: Chess Champion D Gukesh shaves head at Tirumala Temple- know tradition

description: Elon Musk shared an old video of Barack Obama, where the former president discusses reducing government waste and unnecessary spending. In the video, Obama highlights the importance of eliminating pointless expenses and mentions specific examples, stressing the need for efficient budget management.
title: Elon Musk shares Barack Obama’s old 'OMG video' on 'stupid spending’

description: Two police officers and a civilian died when a speeding Volkswagen Polo crashed into them at a police check post in Chandigarh during Holi celebrations. The car driver and his friends were also injured, and liquor bottles were found in their vehicle. Senior police officials visited the scene to investigate.
title: High-speed car kills 2 cops, civilian at police check post in Chandigarh

description: The Tamil Nadu government presented the 2025-26 budget with key welfare initiatives, including fare-free bus travel for women and monthly financial support. Amid the budget session, AIADMK protested over corruption allegations. Significant funds were allocated for housing, education, and new infrastructure projects.
title: Metro expansions, new airport: Key takeaways from Tamil Nadu Budget

description: The driver of Jaffar Express recounted the terror when BLA militants attacked the train, killing 21 civilians and 4 soldiers. The militants exploded a bomb under the engine, causing a derailment. The Pakistani military rescued 340 passengers after a two-day standoff, claiming 33 attackers were killed. The BLA disputed this, alleging they still hold hostages.
title: 'Mistook us for dead': Pakistan train driver recalls 36-hour terror siege

description: Karnataka High Court granted B.S. Yediyurappa interim relief by staying the summons in a POCSO Act case, requiring his appearance on March 15. The court emphasized a comprehensive investigation and quashing the charge sheet. Yediyurappa faces allegations of inappropriate touching and harassment but denies all charges, citing political motivations and readiness to face legal proceedings.
title: POCSO case: Karnataka HC grants interim relief to former CM BS Yediyurappa

description: Kannada actress Ranya Rao was arrested for allegedly smuggling over 14 kg of gold after traveling to Dubai four times within 15 days. Her associate, Tarun Raju, was remanded to 15 days of judicial custody for his role in facilitating the purchase of the gold.
title: Ranya Rao gold smuggling case: Accused Tarun Raju sent to 15-day judicial custody

description: Australia’s young all-rounder, Cooper Connolly, had a memorable ICC Champions Trophy semi-final debut against India. Despite an early dismissal by Mohammed Shami and dropping a catch, Connolly took Rohit Sharma's wicket, marking a significant achievement. Reflecting on the experience, he remains optimistic and eager to seize more opportunities at the international level.
title: 'Shami is a world-class player for a reason': Young Aussie rookie in awe of India pacer

description: Arvind Kejriwal’s Vipassana retreat in Punjab may signal a strategic shift for AAP, potentially involving party reshuffles ahead of the 2027 Punjab Assembly elections. While some speculate on internal meetings, AAP dismisses these as opposition rumors without substantiated development agendas.
title: Silent retreat, loud speculations: Is Kejriwal gearing up for Punjab elections?

description: Australian spinner Matthew Kuhnemann has been cleared to bowl after his action was questioned post-Sri Lanka tour. His 16-wicket haul led Australia to a 2-0 win. Kuhnemann was confident about his action and his experience. Despite missing one domestic game, he used the break to recover. Now, he's eyeing a spot on the West Indies tour.
title: 'There was no doubt': Australia spinner after clearing bowling action test

description: Two Japanese tourists were detained in China for two weeks for taking inappropriate photos at the Great Wall, with a man exposing his buttocks while a woman took pictures. After their detention, they were deported back to Japan, sparking outrage in China and leading to significant backlash on social media.
title: Two Japanese tourists detained for taking ‘indecent’ photos at Great Wall of China

description: A video of New Zealand Prime Minister Christopher Luxon celebrating Holi at ISKCON Auckland has resurfaced online. Luxon, set to visit India from March 16-20, aims to enhance trade and investment ties. He will meet with Prime Minister Narendra Modi, President Droupadi Murmu, and other leaders, emphasizing his admiration for India.
title: Watch: Video of New Zealand PM Christopher Luxon playing holi goes viral

description: US Vice President JD Vance addressed key issues including the deportation of green card holders, immigration enforcement, and border security on 'The Ingraham Angle.' He discussed the administration's efforts to reduce illegal migration, strengthen the economy, and implement 'America first' trade policies. Vance also highlighted the administration's commitment to tackling national security threats posed by non-citizens.
title: 'We'll see some get deported': What US VP said about green card holders
What will be India's approach to trade talks with US?

description: Sultana Begum, the great-granddaughter-in-law of the last Mughal emperor Bahadur Shah Zafar, lives in a Kolkata slum in stark contrast to her royal heritage. She faces financial hardships, surviving on a meager pension, with little government support. Human rights activists have highlighted her plight, indicative of the neglect experienced by descendants of India's former aristocracy.
title: Great-granddaughter of Mughal emperor Bahadur Shah Zafar is alive

description: An Ordnance Factory employee, Ravindra Kumar, was arrested by the Uttar Pradesh ATS for allegedly leaking classified defense information to a Pakistani intelligence handler posing as Neha Sharma. He shared sensitive documents via WhatsApp, endangering national security. Authorities continue to investigate the extent of the security breach.
title: Honeytrapped on Facebook: Ordnance factory worker held for leaking secrets to Pak's ISI

description: Apple CEO Tim Cook continues his tradition of celebrating cultural festivals by wishing everyone a happy Holi with a colorful photo taken on an iPhone, shared on X. The image by Kushagra Tiwari is part of Apple’s #ShotOniPhone campaign, promoting creative iPhone photography.
title: Apple CEO celebrates Holi with iPhone photo by Kushagra Tiwari

description: Veteran actor Deb Mukherjee, father of director Ayan Mukerji, passed away at 83. Known for films like 'Abhinetri' and 'Kaminey,' he had been hospitalized and died on March 14. Mukherjee's familial ties include actresses Kajol and Rani Mukerji. His contributions to Indian cinema and connection to Bollywood's Mukherjee-Samarth family are notable.
title: Director Ayan Mukerji’s father, , veteran actor Deb Mukherjee, passes away

description: An Amravati-bound train collided with a truck illegally crossing closed railway tracks in Jalgaon, Maharashtra. No injuries were reported, but the collision disrupted the schedules of five trains, including the Mumbai-Amravati Express. The incident caused significant damage to railway infrastructure. Repair work is underway, and legal action may be taken against the truck driver.
title: Train collides with truck at closed level crossing in Maharashtra's Jalgaon

description: A 23-year-old law student, Rakshit Chaurasia, allegedly in a drunken state, hit three vehicles, injuring eight and killing one in Vadodara. Chaurasia was driving while his friend Meet Chauhan owned the car. Chaurasia and Chauhan face charges, including culpable homicide. The deceased woman is identified as Hemali Patel, with her husband critically injured.
title: 'Another round': 23-yr old rams car into 3 vehicles, kills woman, injures 8 others

description: A 42-year-old woman and her two daughters were found dead from suspected poisoning in their Delhi flat, likely due to financial distress. The mother had previously been jailed for murder, and the family faced ongoing economic hardships. Neighbours described them as reclusive and seldom interacted.
title: 'Pending rent, no job, murder of partner': Woman 'kills' daughters, then herself

description: US President Donald Trump suggested that the United States may eventually annex Greenland, highlighting its importance for international security. His comments came amid Greenland's parliamentary elections, where the Demokraatit Party, which opposes Trump's proposal, secured an unexpected victory.
title: Trump again suggests US could annex Greenland, hints at Nato’s role

description: US Rep. Chuck Edwards faced a confrontational crowd in Asheville, North Carolina, with attendees protesting Trump administration policies and initiatives. Despite interruptions, Edwards discussed hurricane recovery efforts, government reductions, and support for Ukraine, while maintaining support for Trump and addressing concerns about Elon Musk's role in government security.
title: Watch: GOP town hall sees heated exchange crowd and Rep. Chuck Edward

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, President Draupadi Murmu, Union home minister Amit Shah, and Congress MP Rahul Gandhi extended their Holi greetings, emphasizing themes of unity, harmony, progress, and prosperity. The leaders highlighted the significance of Holi in deepening bonds among citizens and celebrating India's cultural heritage, infusing joy, and bringing new enthusiasm into everyone's lives.
title: 'Will deepen the colours of unity': PM Modi extends Holi wishes

description: Axar Patel has been named the new captain of Delhi Capitals for the upcoming IPL season. The experienced all-rounder, who has played 150 IPL matches, replaces Rishabh Pant. Delhi Capitals are the last team to announce their captain, with KL Rahul among the key players expected to support Axar’s leadership going into the 2025 season.
title: Axar Patel named Delhi Capitals captain for IPL 2025

description: Ukrainian President Zelenskyy has criticized Russian President Putin for his hesitancy regarding the US-proposed 30-day ceasefire. Zelenskyy accuses Putin of using manipulation and creating complications to indirectly refuse the ceasefire, while asserting that Russia prefers to prolong the conflict despite the opportunity for peace.
title: 'Putin preparing refusal but afraid to tell Trump': Zelenskyy on Ukraine truce

description: CBI has filed an FIR in Delhi regarding a gold-smuggling case allegedly involving actor Ranya Rao, without naming any specific individuals but identifying "unknown public servants" and "unknown private persons" as suspects. This step has intensified the investigation, potentially uncovering deep-rooted corruption within government circles.
title: Ranya Rao case: What does blank ‘accused column’ in CBI FIR mean for netas & babus

description: IIT Guwahati Professor D Udaya Kumar, who designed the Indian rupee symbol, distanced himself from the controversy over Tamil Nadu's decision to replace the Devanagari symbol with a Tamil letter in its budget logo. The state government's move is part of a larger language policy dispute with the central government. Kumar emphasized the autonomy of state decisions.
title: Rupee symbol designer reacts to Stalin govt using Tamil letter in Budget

description: Lionel Messi made a spectacular return for Inter Miami, scoring in a 2-0 win over Cavalier FC, securing a 4-0 aggregate victory in the CONCACAF Champions Cup. Messi's goal and Luis Suárez's penalty confirmed Miami's quarter-final spot. Coach Mascherano praised Messi's impact, while Cavalier's spirited performance was commended despite the loss.
title: Watch: Messi's late strike sends Miami into Champions Cup quarters

description: India has strongly rejected Pakistan's allegations of involvement in the Balochistan train hijacking, pointing out Pakistan's issues with internal terrorism. Accusations emerged after the Balochistan Liberation Army seized the Jaffar Express, resulting in 58 deaths. Afghanistan also denied Pakistan's claims, urging Islamabad to address its own security challenges.
title: 'Whole world knows where ... ': India slams Pak’s allegation on train hijacking

description: Yuzvendra Chahal will return to Northamptonshire for the 2025 County Championship after impressive performances in 2024. The India leg-spinner, joining post-IPL 2025, will play until season-end. Chahal's 2024 stint saw him take 19 wickets in four first-class games. New head coach Darren Lehmann and CEO Ray Payne expressed enthusiasm for his return.
title: Chahal to re-join Northamptonshire for 2025 County season after IPL

description: Vicky Kaushal's historical drama 'Chhaava' has grossed Rs 540.45 Cr over four weeks. The movie, directed by Laxman Utekar, earned significantly in the first two weeks but saw a dip in collections thereafter. It had a notable 90% growth boost on Women's Day.
title: 'Chhaava' box office day 28: Vicky Kaushal starrer misses Rs 550 crore mark

description: Glenn McGrath supports Jasprit Bumrah's recovery from a back injury and stresses the importance of smart management due to his age. Bumrah's experience makes him invaluable to India. McGrath commends India for their smart play in the Champions Trophy, rejecting claims of unfair advantage. India's strong white-ball cricket is noted with emphasis on the influence of IPL.
title: 'Don't think India had unfair advantage': McGrath on Dubai controversy

description: Russian President Vladimir Putin expressed gratitude to leaders including India's PM Modi and US President Trump for their efforts to end the Russia-Ukraine conflict. Putin agreed to a ceasefire if it leads to long-term peace, appreciating international support for peaceful resolution. PM Modi emphasized India's active role and reiterated the importance of negotiation over warfare.
title: 'Have enough of our own ... ': Putin acknowledges Trump, PM Modi’s role in Ukraine talks

description: Stock market holidays 2025: Indian stock exchanges BSE and NSE will close on Friday for Holi, creating an extended weekend. With 14 holidays in 2025, trading is suspended for various significant occasions, including Ramzan Id this month.
title: Stock market holidays: Are BSE and NSE closed for trading on Holi ?

description: A federal judge in San Francisco has ordered the Trump administration to reinstate numerous dismissed probationary workers, asserting that the terminations were executed without proper authority. The administration plans to appeal the ruling, while multiple lawsuits against these dismissals are ongoing.
title: US judge orders Trump admin to reinstate fired govt employees

description: A mansion built for former Andhra Pradesh Chief Minister Jagan Mohan Reddy in Visakhapatnam is facing scrutiny for its opulent design and high costs. Once intended as a camp office, the project has evolved through various stages, now sparking a debate on its usage and the ethics of public spending. The extravagance compares to Arvind Kejriwal's controversial residence renovation.
title: Watch: A look inside ex-Andhra CM Jagan Reddy’s lavish sea-facing mansion

description: Holi 2025, the festival of colors, marks the arrival of spring and the triumph of good over evil. People globally exchange heartfelt messages, wishes, and greetings, spreading happiness and positivity among friends, family, and loved ones. Celebrate the spirit of togetherness with joy and vibrant colors.
title: 75+ Holi messages, greetings, wishes, and quotes
Fire erupts on American Airlines plane at Denver Airport

description: Jeremy Stephens is set to return to the UFC after over three years, with a fight in Des Moines, Iowa against Mason Jones on May 3. Now 38, Stephens seeks a resurgence after recent successes in various combat sports, including a TKO win in bare-knuckle fighting.
title: Jeremy Stephens signs with UFC Again: Faces Mason Jones at UFC Des Moines

description: On Feb 15, New Delhi railway station sold 13,000 more general tickets than average, coinciding with a tragic crowd rush resulting in 18 deaths. Despite operating five special trains, the rush exceeded expectations. An inquiry is ongoing, and officials have been transferred. Ticket procurement practices and alternatives were also highlighted by Railway Minister Ashwini Vaishnaw.
title: 13,000 more general tickets than daily average sold at NDLS on stampede day: Vaishnaw

description: The Union law ministry has instructed a district court in Ahmedabad to deliver a summons issued by the US Securities and Exchange Commission to Gautam Adani concerning alleged securities fraud and a $265 million bribery scheme. This summons requires Adani or his legal representatives to appear in the US court.
title: Centre asks Ahmedabad court to deliver US regulator’s summons to Adani

description: The Central Government has requested Starlink, Elon Musk's satellite venture, to establish a control centre in India. This measure will enable the suspension or shutdown of communications services in sensitive areas when needed to maintain law and order. Additionally, call interceptions by law enforcement agencies must be facilitated. Starlink is working with Reliance Jio and Airtel for network enhancements.
title: Centre sets tough conditions for India entry by Starlink

description: Young farmer awardee Kailash Arjun Nagare dies by suicide after consuming poison, citing government inaction on irrigation water demands. His death stirs massive unrest among local farmers, leading to protests and demands for accountability from the administration.
title: Award-winning farmer dies by suicide, blames Maharashtra government

description: NR Narayana Murthy, co-founder of Infosys, emphasized at TiECon Mumbai that many so-called AI systems in India are merely traditional programming. He stressed the importance of genuine AI, which relies on machine learning and deep learning. Murthy acknowledged AI's potential for job displacement but highlighted its economic benefits.
title: Somehow it has become a fashion in India to ...: Narayana Murthy

description: A woman named Neha in Greater Noida was allegedly strangled to death by her father and brother for marrying someone from a different caste. They cremated her body swiftly. Neha's husband, Suraj, alerted the police after learning about her death. The father and brother were arrested following the confession. An FIR has been registered for murder.
title: Day after wedding, woman strangled to death by family for marrying man she loved

description: Telangana police, led by the Cyber Security Bureau, have registered nine FIRs against agents involved in trafficking individuals into Myanmar's cybercrime hubs. The crackdown follows the return of 24 victims and focuses on deceptive recruitment and coercion tactics used via social media. Further cases and identifications are underway.
title: 'My identity was erased': How Telangana man ended up in Myanmar cybercrime den

description: In Sabarkantha district, a man was abducted, beaten, and paraded naked by the husband and relatives of a woman he allegedly had an affair with. The incident occurred on March 11 in Chadasana village. The police have arrested seven people. The victim was forced to apologize in writing and his mobile was stolen.
title: Man paraded naked, beaten up over affair in Gujarat

description: In Dehradun, police identified a hit-and-run vehicle by finding a broken Mercedes logo and using CCTV footage. The car, registered in Chandigarh, led them to nine potential matches. Further investigation and service records confirmed the culprit vehicle, ultimately tracing it back to the accused, Vansh Katyal, through his brother-in-law who owned the car.
title: How broken Mercedes logo, CCTV tech helped crack Dehradun accident case

description: Stanford students are showing increasing interest in defense technology careers, influenced by coursework and new campus initiatives. This marks a shift from past sentiments, as graduates now seek roles at firms like Palantir and Anduril, and launch their own defense startups. The Gordian Knot Center supports this growing enthusiasm.
title: Peter Theil’s Palantir and others make gov-tech cool again at Stanford
